From Soup: 38 For a small mean free path the same set of particles interact over several Δ t with each other before leaving this cell and hence they remain correlated over several Δ t . If one imposes a flow field the degree of correlation and therefore the transport coefficients depends on the magnitude of the flow field. The violated Galilean invariance can be restored if all particle positions are shifted by a random vector before the collision step. 19
